# Intake & document extraction

- **PDF text**: `pdfParser.ts` chooses `GoogleDocumentAiProvider` when `UPLOAD_PDF_PROVIDER=google-document-ai` (requires GCP processor + ADC); otherwise `FallbackPdfExtractionProvider` (pdf-parse).
- **Gemini**: `extractIntakeFromGemini` / `geminiExtractionService` — keep prompt rules in sync with `rowClassifierService.shouldKeepNormalizedLine` and `intakeTextGuards` (contact/boilerplate, section headers, pricing disclaimers).
- **Normalization**: Use `normalizeIntakeUnit` from `intakeNormalization.ts` when fixing units from LLM or spreadsheets; extend `UNIT_ALIASES` for new OCR patterns instead of one-off fixes in components.
- **Validator**: `validateNormalizedItems` drops non-scope lines and canonicalizes units — add new drop rules via shared guards in `intakeTextGuards.ts`, not duplicated regex in the UI.
- **Pipeline**: `intakePipeline.ts` maps Gemini lines to `NormalizedIntakeLine`; use `as NormalizedIntakeLine[]` after `.filter` when TypeScript narrows optional fields incorrectly.
- **Division 10 bid reasoning**: Packaged knowledge lives under `data/div10-bid-reasoning/` (JSON + CSV + playbook). `bidReasoning/div10BidReasoningService.ts` loads `div10_bid_reasoning_knowledge.json`, augments the Gemini prompt, merges commercial-clause assumptions in `intakePipeline`, drops commercial/metadata lines via `rowClassifierService` (`matchesDiv10CommercialOrMetadataLine`), and appends install hidden-scope hints to line notes. Extend the JSON for new block types or phrases; keep server-only (do not import from shared client code).
